<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6d774e8-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53512"><num value="53512">§ 53512.</num><heading> FIFO and LIFO withdrawals</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6d774e9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53512/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">FIFO</inline>.—</heading><content>Except as provided in subsection (b), an amount withdrawn from an account under this chapter shall be treated as withdrawn on a first-in-first-out basis.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf6d774ea-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53512/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><heading> <inline class="small-caps">LIFO</inline>.—</heading><chapeau>An amount withdrawn from an account under this chapter shall be treated as withdrawn on a last-in-first-out basis if it is—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6d774eb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53512/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> a nonqualified withdrawal for research, development, and design expenses incident to new and advanced vessel design, machinery, and equipment; or</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idf6d774ec-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s53512/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> an amount treated as a nonqualified withdrawal under <ref href="/us/usc/t46/s53510/d">section 53510(d) of this title</ref>.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf6d774ed-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/c">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(c)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1599">120 Stat. 1599</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
